250 g Ground Turkey
350 g Cheese Tortellini
113 g Mirepoix
4 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
1 tbsp Chicken Stock Powder
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
28 g Baby Spinach
1 unit(s) Zucchini
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Heat a large non-stick pan over high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then turkey and mirepoix. Season with salt, pepper and half the Zesty Garlic Blend.
Cook, stirring often, until veggies are tender-crisp and turkey is cooked through, 3-5 min.**
While turkey cooks, halve zucchini lengthwise, then cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.

Transfer turkey mixture to a bowl.
Reheat pot over medium heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil and zucchini. Season with salt, pepper and remaining Zesty Garlic Blend. Cook, stirring often, until zucchini is tender-crisp and lightly golden, 1-2 min.

Add turkey mixture, tomato sauce base, stock powder, tortellini and 2 1/2 cups (4 cups) water to the pot with zucchini. Bring to a boil over high. Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies and tortellini are tender, 4-6 min.
Add spinach. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to mix. (TIP: For a lighter soup consistency, add water, 1/4 cup at a time, if desired.)

Divide soup between bowls.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.

If you've opted to get turkey, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the sausage.**